---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Intelligent Document Processing | Sentinel Nexus"
  description="Extract, classify, and process unstructured data from documents at scale. AI-powered IDP transforms invoices, contracts, forms, and correspondence into structured, actionable information."
>
  <section class="hero-service">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/ai-implementation">AI Implementation</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Intelligent Document Processing</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>Intelligent Document Processing</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Turn Unstructured Documents into Structured Intelligence</p>
      <p class="hero-description">
        Traditional OCR and template-based extraction fail with real-world documents. We deploy AI-powered document processing that understands context, adapts to variation, and continuously improves—transforming your document-heavy workflows at scale.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>Beyond Basic OCR</h2>
        <p>
          Organizations drown in documents—invoices, contracts, claims, regulatory filings, correspondence. Traditional document processing relies on rigid templates and rule-based extraction that break the moment a vendor changes their invoice layout or a new form variant appears.
        </p>
        <p>
          The result: manual data entry bottlenecks, processing delays, error rates that compound downstream, and skilled staff spending hours on work that should take seconds. Template-based systems can't handle the variation, ambiguity, and context-dependence that characterize real-world documents.
        </p>
        <p>
          Intelligent Document Processing changes the equation. By combining computer vision, natural language understanding, and domain-specific AI models, IDP systems comprehend documents the way humans do—understanding context, inferring meaning from layout and language, and adapting to new formats without reprogramming.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our IDP Methodology</h2>

      <div class="characteristics-grid">
        <div class="char-card">
          <div class="char-number">01</div>
          <h3>Document Assessment and Classification</h3>
          <p>Analyze your document inventory: types, volumes, formats, variation, and complexity. Classify documents by processing difficulty and build a prioritized implementation roadmap.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <div class="char-number">02</div>
          <h3>Extraction Model Design</h3>
          <p>Select and configure the right AI approach for each document type—from pre-trained models for standard formats to custom-trained extractors for specialized or proprietary documents.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <div class="char-number">03</div>
          <h3>Training and Fine-Tuning</h3>
          <p>Train models on your actual documents, incorporating domain terminology, layout patterns, and business rules. Iteratively refine until extraction accuracy meets production thresholds.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <div class="char-number">04</div>
          <h3>Workflow Integration</h3>
          <p>Connect IDP outputs to downstream systems—ERP, accounting, case management, databases—with automated routing, approval workflows, and exception handling built in.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <div class="char-number">05</div>
          <h3>Validation and QA</h3>
          <p>Implement confidence scoring, human-in-the-loop review for low-confidence extractions, and automated quality checks that catch errors before they propagate downstream.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <div class="char-number">06</div>
          <h3>Continuous Learning</h3>
          <p>Deploy feedback loops where corrections and edge cases continuously improve model accuracy. Monitor extraction quality over time and retrain as document formats evolve.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Document Processing Use Cases</h2>

      <div class="usecases-grid">
        <div class="usecase-card">
          <h3>Invoice and AP Processing</h3>
          <p>Automate invoice capture, line-item extraction, PO matching, and approval routing—handling multi-format invoices from hundreds of vendors without template maintenance.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="usecase-card">
          <h3>Contract Analysis</h3>
          <p>Extract key terms, obligations, dates, and clauses from contracts at scale. Enable risk identification, compliance checking, and searchable contract intelligence across your portfolio.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="usecase-card">
          <h3>Claims Processing</h3>
          <p>Accelerate insurance, warranty, and benefits claims by automatically extracting claim details, supporting documentation, and relevant evidence for faster adjudication.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="usecase-card">
          <h3>Regulatory Document Review</h3>
          <p>Process regulatory filings, compliance documents, and audit materials—extracting requirements, identifying changes, and flagging items that need human review.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="usecase-card">
          <h3>Mail and Correspondence Triage</h3>
          <p>Classify incoming mail and correspondence by type, urgency, and intent. Route to the right team, extract actionable information, and trigger appropriate workflows automatically.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="usecase-card">
          <h3>Forms and Applications</h3>
          <p>Process application forms, onboarding documents, and intake paperwork—handling handwriting, checkboxes, signatures, and varying layouts with high accuracy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Security and Governance Built In</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">Document processing often involves sensitive data. Every IDP solution we build embeds privacy, security, and compliance from the ground up.</p>

      <div class="characteristics-grid">
        <div class="char-card">
          <h3>Data Privacy</h3>
          <p>Documents are processed with strict data handling controls—encryption at rest and in transit, secure processing environments, and configurable data retention policies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <h3>PII Handling</h3>
          <p>Automatic detection and protection of personally identifiable information with redaction, masking, and access controls aligned to your data classification policies.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <h3>Audit Trails</h3>
          <p>Complete traceability from document ingestion through extraction, validation, and downstream delivery—every decision and data transformation is logged and reviewable.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="char-card">
          <h3>Compliance Alignment</h3>
          <p>IDP architectures designed to meet HIPAA, GDPR, SOC 2, and industry-specific requirements with built-in controls for data residency, retention, and access governance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-block">
        <h2>IDP as Part of Your AI Strategy</h2>
        <p>
          Intelligent Document Processing is most powerful when it feeds into broader automation and governance initiatives. Extracted data powers downstream workflows, analytics, and decision-making—multiplying the value of every document your organization processes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our IDP implementations are designed to integrate seamlessly with your existing systems and complement your broader AI program.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="pillars-callout">
        <div class="pillar-link">
          <h4>Workflow Automation</h4>
          <p>Feed extracted document data directly into intelligent workflows that route, approve, and act on information automatically.</p>
          <a href="/ai-implementation/workflow-automation-process-redesign">Learn about Workflow Automation &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-link">
          <h4>AI Governance</h4>
          <p>Ensure your document processing pipelines meet regulatory requirements with built-in governance and compliance frameworks.</p>
          <a href="/ai-governance">Explore AI Governance &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to transform your document workflows?</h2>
      <p>Let's assess your document landscape and build intelligent processing that eliminates manual bottlenecks.</p>
      <a href="/#contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-large" data-umami-event="{Intelligent Document Processing | Start a Conversation Btn}">Start a Conversation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-service {
    padding: 10rem 0 4rem;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at top, rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.15) 0%, var(--color-bg) 70%);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .hero-service h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .hero-description {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .section-dark {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-intro {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: -1rem auto 2rem;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
  }

  .content-block {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .content-block h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .content-block p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .characteristics-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .char-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .char-number {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
    opacity: 0.6;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .char-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .char-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .usecases-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .usecase-card {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .usecase-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
  }

  .usecase-card p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .pillars-callout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .pillar-link {
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .pillar-link h4 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .pillar-link p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .pillar-link a {
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease;
  }

  .pillar-link a:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .section-cta {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-accent-1) 0%, #1e40af 100%);
    text-align: center;
    padding: 5rem 0;
  }

  .section-cta h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .section-cta p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .section-cta .btn-primary {
    background: white;
    color: var(--color-accent-1);
  }

  .section-cta .btn-primary:hover {
    background: #f0f0f0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero-service {
      padding: 8rem 0 3rem;
    }

    .characteristics-grid,
    .usecases-grid,
    .pillars-callout {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
